  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry</strong> <strong>tomatoes </strong>roughly</p><p>Cut your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676911914076-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676911914076-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676911914076-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676911914076-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1676911914076-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676911924662-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676911924662-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676911924662-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676911924662-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1676911924662-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the leek is cooking, zest your<strong> lemon[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter), then cut in half</p><p>Peel <strong>half</strong> your<strong> Italian hard cheese </strong>until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings and grate the rest</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676911928942-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676911928942-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676911928942-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676911928942-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1676911928942-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the<strong> chopped tomatoes </strong>to the pan with the<strong> chopped garlic</strong>, most of the<strong> chopped chilli</strong> (can’t handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 5-6 min or until the tomatoes have softened, then remove from the heat and set aside</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676911933002-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676911933002-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676911933002-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676911933002-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1676911933002-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 8 min or until tender</p><p>After the initial 8 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and top with your<strong> flaked almonds</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 3-4 min or until the almonds are golden</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676911937489-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676911937489-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676911937489-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676911937489-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1676911937489-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Break your <strong>lasagne sheets </strong>into medium-sized pieces and add them to the boiling water, stirring to separate the pasta pieces – these are your <strong>pasta stracci</strong></p><p>Cook for 7-9 min, stirring from time to time to prevent the pasta from sticking, then drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pasta stracci</strong>,<strong> </strong>reserving a little <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676911943128-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676911943128-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676911943128-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676911943128-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1676911943128-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan with the tomatoes to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>crab meat</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you’ll use the shavings later!), <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pasta stracci</strong> and a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min, then remove from the heat and stir through your <strong>soft cheese</strong>,<strong> </strong>most of the <strong>lemon zest</strong>, a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>creamy crab & chilli stracci</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676911949292-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676911949292-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676911949292-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676911949292-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1676911949292-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the<strong> remaining lemon </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Serve the <strong>creamy crab & chilli stracci</strong> topped with the <strong>remaining lemon zest</strong>,<strong> chopped chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and the<strong> cheese shavings</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salad </strong>with the<strong> charred Tenderstem & toasted almonds </strong>to the side, then drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
